svg.title: UML Diagram: Class KeyMember in Context

g.text: UML Diagram: Class KeyMember in Context
- The arrows of the inheritance tree are

a.title: • DataStructureComponent: Role given to a represented variable in the context of a data structure.
a.xlink:title: • DataStructureComponent: Role given to a represented variable in the context of a data structure.

a.title: • Key: Collection of data instances that uniquely identify a collection of data points in a dataset.
a.xlink:title: • Key: Collection of data instances that uniquely identify a collection of data points in a dataset.

a.title: • Descriptor: Use of a code for variable identification in the context of a data structure and a variable descriptor component.
a.xlink:title: • Descriptor: Use of a code for variable identification in the context of a data structure and a variable descriptor component.

a.title: • InstanceValue: Single data instance corresponding to a concept (with a notion of equality defined) being observed, captured, or derived.
a.xlink:title: • InstanceValue: Single data instance corresponding to a concept (with a notion of equality defined) being observed, captured, or derived.

a.title: • TypedString: TypedString combines a type with content defined as a simple string. May be used wherever a simple string needs to support a type definition to clarify its content.
a.xlink:title: • TypedString: TypedString combines a type with content defined as a simple string. May be used wherever a simple string needs to support a type definition to clarify its content.

a.title: • Identifier: Identifier for objects requiring short- or long-lasting referencing and management.
a.xlink:title: • Identifier: Identifier for objects requiring short- or long-lasting referencing and management.

a.title: • WhiteSpaceRule: WhiteSpace constrains the value space of types derived from string.
a.xlink:title: • WhiteSpaceRule: WhiteSpace constrains the value space of types derived from string.

a.title: • ValueDomain: Set of permissible values for a variable (adapted from ISO/IEC 11179).
a.xlink:title: • ValueDomain: Set of permissible values for a variable (adapted from ISO/IEC 11179).

a.title: • DimensionalKeyMember: Single data instance that is part of a dimensional key.
a.xlink:title: • DimensionalKeyMember: Single data instance that is part of a dimensional key.

a.title: • LongMainKeyMember: Single data instance that is part of a long key.
a.xlink:title: • LongMainKeyMember: Single data instance that is part of a long key.

a.title: • Datum: Correspondence of a data instance to the concept it represents.
a.xlink:title: • Datum: Correspondence of a data instance to the concept it represents.

a.title: • InstanceKey: Single-valued key representation produced from the merge of the representations of all key members and a descriptor.
a.xlink:title: • InstanceKey: Single-valued key representation produced from the merge of the representations of all key members and a descriptor.

a.title: • WideKeyMember: Single data instance that is part of a wide key.
a.xlink:title: • WideKeyMember: Single data instance that is part of a wide key.

a.title: • MainKeyMember: Identifies the unit of interest, either a statistical unit or a population, via identifier or dimension components, respectively, plus an optional contextual component. If neither identifier nor dimension components are present, then a synthetic id component is used.
a.xlink:title: • MainKeyMember: Identifies the unit of interest, either a statistical unit or a population, via identifier or dimension components, respectively, plus an optional contextual component. If neither identifier nor dimension components are present, then a synthetic id component is used.
